            <title>[OWB-660] WebBeansContext #activateContext for SessionScoped.class doesn&apos;t set the ThreadLocal</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OWB-660</link>
                <project id="12310844" key="OWB">OpenWebBeans</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The WebBeansContext #activateContext(SessionScoped.class) method doesn&apos;t set the ThreadLocal which holds the current SessionContext. This creates quite a few problems if other plugins or Extensions like to activate the SessionContext in web applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
